"{\"uid\": \"nzherald.co.nz-travel-the-best-beaches-in-france-for-post-paris-olympics-rr-NRLZGGMCMJFVFPHCXRLIDIUBIA\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The French do not want you to know about their best beaches.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 60, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999220238655, \"rank\": 7.79761993923308e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Photo / Getty Images  Whether you prefer stretching out in the sun with a chilled glass ofwineor charging across the sand on a go-kart with a sail, there is a beach in France for everyone, writes Anna Richards.\", \"from\": 61, \"to\": 271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 229, \"end\": 235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 257, \"end\": 270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Richards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Richards\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Richards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Richards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France is not like the Seychelles.\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seychelles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.400849823853688e-30, \"text\": \"Seychelles\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seychelles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seychelles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Itsbeachesdon't dominate the windowdisplays of high street travel agents, or take over every Windows screensaver.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft_Windows\", \"score\": 0.9999997353234343, \"rank\": 2.6414881726682034e-07, \"text\": \"Windows\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft_Windows\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Microsoft_Windows\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are not (many) swaying palms; you will not be diving with manta rays.\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, they are spectacularly varied.\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Subtropical archipelagos, goat tracks down limestone cliffs and sunsetsurfsbefore tucking into a hefty marmite (casserole) of moules frites - it's all here.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beaches in France often give the impression of being extremely polished.\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 707, \"end\": 713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The best-known are often synonymous with celebrities.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brigitte Bardot dancing topless at Pampelonne Beach in Saint-Tropez.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 832, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Bardot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.031340088157612e-54, \"text\": \"Bardot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Bardot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brigitte_Bardot\"}, {\"begin\": 858, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampelonne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pampelonne\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampelonne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pampelonne\"}, {\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Tropez\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.456002294116266e-42, \"text\": \"Saint-Tropez\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Tropez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Tropez\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The star-studded boardwalk of Deauville, where Coco Chanel owned a boutique.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deauville\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.879836898686762e-24, \"text\": \"Deauville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deauville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Deauville\"}, {\"begin\": 939, \"end\": 950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Chanel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.916815843834656e-49, \"text\": \"Coco Chanel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q3501317\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Chanel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Chanel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cannes, where the red carpet is graced by anyone who is anyone in thefilmindustry each May.\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 1060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:5 best beach towns in France for summer holidays  Always a beach bum at heart, I spent much of the past two years writing a watersports guide to France, which lumbered me with the onerous task of visiting many of France's most fabulous beaches.\", \"from\": 1062, \"to\": 1316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These are not the beaches you will have seen on TV.\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These are the beaches the French would rather you did not know about.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.999999220238655, \"rank\": 7.79761993923308e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's strange that arguably the most tropical-looking place inFranceis in the north.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At their peak, at the end of the 19th century, just 85 people lived on the Gl\\u00e9nan Islands.\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now they are uninhabited and the people who visit are eithertouristsor aspiring sailors taking classes at the world-famous Gl\\u00e9nans sailing school.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are nine islands in the archipelago and all the white sand beaches are wonderful, but my favourite is Plage de Gl\\u00e9nan-Bananec, the narrow strip of sand on \\u00cele Saint-Nicolas that links it with the next island, Bananec.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How to get there:From Paris,take the trainor drive to Concarneau (five hours).\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2009, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.943817145788211e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2041, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concarneau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3267724923381685e-14, \"text\": \"Concarneau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concarneau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concarneau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From here, Vedettes de l'Odet has twice-daily services to the Gl\\u00e9nan Islands (mid-April to mid-September).\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where to stay:Thalasso Resort, Concarneau, has a vast spa complex and is well-placed for the ferry to the Gl\\u00e9nans.\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2205, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concarneau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3267724923381685e-14, \"text\": \"Concarneau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concarneau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concarneau\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From \\u20ac164/night (NZ$287)  France's southeast does not have so many sandy beaches but the limestone cliffs and calanques (rocky inlets) add an altogether different character.Beach town Cap d'Ailhas under 5000 residents and an abundance of Scots pines framed by towering cliffs.\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2527, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\", \"score\": 0.9992148659216566, \"rank\": 0.0007757334744189525, \"text\": \"Scots\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scotland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's possible to get here on foot from Nice along the coast path.\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2605, \"end\": 2609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.518701448890417e-22, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The beach is small but, if it gets crowded, bask on one of the rocks, where you can jump straight into crystal cool water and sizzle on the stone like a frying egg afterwards.\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Laid-back little beach restaurants sell fresh seafood and arancini.\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arancini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"arancini\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arancini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arancini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How to get there:The closestairportis Nice, a 20-minute train ride from Cap-d'Ail.\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2915, \"end\": 2919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.518701448890417e-22, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where to stay:Kaleidoscopic in colour, Mama Shelter, Nice, is the perfect place for an after-beach cocktail.\", \"from\": 2961, \"to\": 3069, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3000, \"end\": 3012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mama Shelter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor\"}, {\"begin\": 3014, \"end\": 3018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.518701448890417e-22, \"text\": \"Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From \\u20ac233/night.\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(NZ$408)  Choosing the best beach in Corsica is an impossible task, not least because of the sheer quantity (there are around 200 named beaches on this Mediterranean island, but I suspect the true number is much higher).\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Piantarella Beach, a sheltered little cove, even when the sea whips into a frenzy, has sand so fine it looks as though it has been sieved.\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The splintered rocky islands that you see just offshore are the outcrops of the Lavezzi Islands, a protected archipelago between Corsica and Sardinia.\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3527, \"end\": 3542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lavezzi_archipelago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lavezzi Islands\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lavezzi_archipelago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lavezzi_archipelago\"}, {\"begin\": 3588, \"end\": 3596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardinia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6156321856422628e-21, \"text\": \"Sardinia\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardinia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardinia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The one closest to the beach is a nesting ground for several bird species so, rather than alighting, hire a paddleboard from Bonif'Kayak on the beach and paddle out around it to observe them from the water.\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How to get there:Domestic flights from Paris Orly go to Figari - South Corsica Airport.\", \"from\": 3806, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3845, \"end\": 3855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orly_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Orly\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orly_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orly_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 3862, \"end\": 3868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figari\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Figari\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figari\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figari\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hire a car from the airport to drive the 30km to Piantarella.\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Where to stay:H\\u00f4tel Colomba, in the heart of Bonifacio, has a great restaurant with sea views.\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3977, \"end\": 3984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colomba\", \"score\": 0.9999967724277002, \"rank\": 3.2265496547464883e-06, \"text\": \"Colomba\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colomba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colomba\"}, {\"begin\": 4002, \"end\": 4011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strait_of_Bonifacio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7999719284839047e-32, \"text\": \"Bonifacio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strait_of_Bonifacio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Strait_of_Bonifacio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From \\u20ac150/night (NZ$262).\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4077, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Southwest France is the surfer's haunt and towns yo-yo between the glitz and glamour of places like Biarritz and sleepy little places where the restaurant floors are often carpeted with sand.\", \"from\": 4079, \"to\": 4270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4079, \"end\": 4095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_West_France_(wine_region)\", \"score\": 0.9999991890102697, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Southwest France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_West_France_(wine_region)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_West_France_(wine_region)\"}, {\"begin\": 4179, \"end\": 4187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Biarritz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.428266550361144e-23, \"text\": \"Biarritz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Biarritz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Biarritz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mimizian Plage, by Plage Remember, is one of the latter.\", \"from\": 4271, \"to\": 4327, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dunes flank the beach, a protective barrier between the rolling waves of the Atlantic.\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sand is caramel in colour, even more so as the sun sets directly over the sea.\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not a spot for swimming and there is little in the way of infrastructure, but to surf in the sunset and enjoy moules frites as the saltwater crystallises on your skin, there is nowhere better.\", \"from\": 4498, \"to\": 4695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How to get there:Plage Remember is a 90-minute drive from Bordeaux (international airport and high-speed train connections to Paris).\", \"from\": 4697, \"to\": 4830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4755, \"end\": 4763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7183822461412492e-14, \"text\": \"Bordeaux\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bordeaux\"}, {\"begin\": 4823, \"end\": 4828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.943817145788211e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where to stay:Friendly little Villa Sunshine runs surf lessons and has boards for hire.\", \"from\": 4832, \"to\": 4919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4868, \"end\": 4876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunlight\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1199158385603794e-39, \"text\": \"Sunshine\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunlight\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunlight\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the crow flies it's directly north of Plage Remember, but driving takes just shy of an hour.\", \"from\": 4920, \"to\": 5015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From \\u20ac55/night (NZ$96).\", \"from\": 5016, \"to\": 5039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If I am honest, the beaches in Hauts-de-France are not the best in the country, although they are some of the biggest.\", \"from\": 5041, \"to\": 5159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Facing onto the English Channel, enormous, slightly muddy-coloured tidal sands stretch for miles at low tide, creating the perfect playground for one of northern France's most peculiar and most entertaining sports: char \\u00e0 voile, or land sailing.\", \"from\": 5160, \"to\": 5405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5322, \"end\": 5328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three-wheeled buggies equipped with sails whip across the flats like a particularly messy version of go-karting as you splash through salt pools and rivulets of water making their way to the sea.\", \"from\": 5406, \"to\": 5601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They can reach speeds of up to 60km/h and the wide open spaces mean the wind comes through at a whack to propel you.\", \"from\": 5602, \"to\": 5718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The town is rather uninspiring but the countryside just further south in the Bay of Somme makes for a much more pleasant stay.\", \"from\": 5719, \"to\": 5845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How to get there:Fort-Mahon-Plage is just under two hours' drive from Lille (international airport, Eurostar services to London and high-speed trains to Paris).\", \"from\": 5847, \"to\": 6007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5864, \"end\": 5880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fort-Mahon-Plage\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fort-Mahon-Plage\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fort-Mahon-Plage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fort-Mahon-Plage\"}, {\"begin\": 5917, \"end\": 5922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"score\": 0.9999999995925464, \"rank\": 3.9985250609928246e-10, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille\"}, {\"begin\": 5947, \"end\": 5955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"score\": 0.9999999993751771, \"rank\": 6.249939269714744e-10, \"text\": \"Eurostar\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eurostar\"}, {\"begin\": 5968, \"end\": 5974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.317736130435225e-16, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 6000, \"end\": 6005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.943817145788211e-33, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where to stay:Skip the rather bleak-looking Fort Mahon town and stay at eco-camp Le Piloti instead, 10km away.\", \"from\": 6009, \"to\": 6119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6053, \"end\": 6063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fort_Mahon\", \"score\": 0.9999999999799911, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fort Mahon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fort_Mahon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fort_Mahon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From \\u20ac128/night (NZ$224) (minimum two-night stay).\", \"from\": 6120, \"to\": 6170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more things to see and do in France, visit france.fr/en  There is always something to celebrate in New Orleans.\", \"from\": 6172, \"to\": 6287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6205, \"end\": 6211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.455759892379324e-23, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6275, \"end\": 6286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Orleans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.245136301234663e-22, \"text\": \"New Orleans\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Orleans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Orleans\"}]}]}"